{"article_id":"5Ha0Yzh2dk3FCKxH","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The country 's most prominent fact checkers fought a losing battle against the flood of fake news during the presidential campaign .","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"Now ,","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"they say ,","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"they have one great hope","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"for preventing an even greater wave of propaganda","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"masquerading as news :","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"Facebook .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Fact checkers say","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"they need the social network in their corner","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"as Donald Trump , a frequent purveyor of misinformation himself , prepares to inherit the White House","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"- and , with it , the world 's biggest megaphone .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"Facebook has come under withering criticism","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"for allowing the dissemination of egregiously fake stories during the campaign ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"with widely shared headlines falsely reporting","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"that Pope Francis had endorsed Trump ' s candidacy","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"and that an FBI agent","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"involved in the Hillary Clinton email investigation","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"was dead in a murder-suicide .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"CEO Mark Zuckerberg ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"after first scoffing","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"that fake news helped swing the election to Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"has pledged to \" take misinformation seriously , ''","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"though he gave no timeline for action","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"and warned about the dangers","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"of his company becoming an arbiter of the truth .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"But fact-check organizations","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"which diligently reported lies and exaggerations during the campaign ,","depth":14},{"id":28,"text":"only to see their work overshadowed by false headlines -","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"argue","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that only Facebook has the reach and influence","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"to address the free flow of fake news .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"And they are pushing the company to make changes now ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"as the weeks tick down to Trump 's inauguration .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"`` Facebook has completely turbo-powered fake news sites , ''","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"says Alexios Mantzarlis , director and editor of the Poynter Institute 's International Fact-Checking Network .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"`` But it 's also probably the first platform","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"that could measure how these things spread ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"and how we could push back . ''","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"Shortly after Election Day , the `` Big Three '' in American fact checking","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"- PolitiFact , a project of the Tampa Bay Times ; FactCheck.org , part of the University of Pennsylvania 's Annenberg Public Policy Center ; and the Washington Post 's Fact Checker -","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"posted an letter to Zuckerberg","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"calling on him to `` start an open conversation on the principles","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"that could underpin a more accurate news ecosystem on its News Feed . ''","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Now fact checkers are getting down to specifics","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"about how Facebook should tackle blatantly fraudulent news .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Fact checkers say","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"they need the social network in their corner","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"as Donald Trump , a frequent purveyor of misinformation himself , prepares to inherit the White House . |","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Getty","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"To start ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"the social network should start removing the most popular false stories from the `` News Feed ''","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"that fills users ' home screens on the site ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"says Mantzarlis .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"He argues","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that kind of filtering would have far-reaching effects ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"because some of the most popular pure hoaxes are reposted and clicked on hundreds of thousands of times ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"sometimes circulating for years .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"`` Let 's not underestimate how important it is to act on the biggest fakes , ''","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Matzarlis says .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"To identify those stories ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Facebook could rely on the human curators","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"who","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"- despite headlines","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"saying","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"Facebook had gone to a completely automated system -","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"still keep an eye on the company-produced `` Trending '' box on the site ,","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"he says .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"`` If something 's been demonstrated to be inaccurate '' by the trending team ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"`` then yank it out of News Feed , ''","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"he says ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"adding","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"such stories could still appear on people 's individual pages","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"but be marked with `` a big red badge '' as fake .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"Another option ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"says Eugene Kiely , director of FactCheck.org ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"is to pair fake stories with prominent fact checks ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"just as many websites today attach `` Related Stories '' to a particular headline .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"`` I 'm concerned about how you go about removing material from these social media sites ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"because I think","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"it 's kind of a dangerous area","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"to get into , ''","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"says Kiely .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"`` But","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"if there 's an article about","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"[ first lady Michelle Obama 's mother ]","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"Marian Robinson getting a pension","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"for watching her grandchildren in the White House for eight years ,","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"there 'd be a related item item right underneath it","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"saying ,","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"'No , grandma 's not getting a pension . ' ''","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"Zuckerberg initially responded to criticism","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"by saying","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"it 's a `` pretty crazy idea '' that fake news on the social network had an impact on the election .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"But in a follow-up post on the topic , he outlined a series of projects","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"the company has underway","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"to deal with fake news ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"including building better technical systems","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"to detect false stories","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"and `` disrupting fake news economics ''","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"by cutting off ad revenue .","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"\" We take misinformation very seriously .","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"We are aware of","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"and have been working on addressing this problem for the past few years , ''","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"a Facebook spokeswoman said","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"when asked for comment .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"`` We know","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"we have more work to do","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"and we ' re hoping","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"we can continue to rely on our community","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"to help us understand what is and is not fake news . \"","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"The fake news issue has shown no signs of dissipating since the election .","depth":3},{"id":112,"text":"Trump has himself helped to disseminate evidence-free claims ,","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"including a tweet","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"claiming","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"that he `` won the popular vote","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"if you deduct the millions of people","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"who voted illegally . ''","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"It 's also become frighteningly real in Washington .","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"Last weekend , a man fired a gun inside an upper northwest Washington , D.C. , pizza place","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"targeted by a false story","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"spread on social media about an alleged Democratic pedophilia ring there , a tale","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"that Michael G. Flynn , the son of Trump 's pick for national security adviser , lent credence to via Twitter .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"The gunman told police","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"he `` wanted to see for himself ''","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"if the restaurant was `` harboring child sex slaves ''","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"-","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"although he acknowledged in a jailhouse interview with The New York Times","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"that \" the intel on this wasn ' t 100 percent . \"","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"Against that backdrop , the fact checkers are pressing Facebook to take concrete steps","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"to identify and weed out hoaxes .","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"View","depth":2},{"id":132,"text":"Clinton decries fake news 'epidemic '","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"Hillary Clinton talks about news on Thursday .","depth":5},{"id":134,"text":"The social network could do a better job","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"enlisting its millions of U.S. users","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"to flag false stories ,","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"Mantzarlis said .","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"The site 's option","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"for reporting `` purposefully fake or deceitful news ''","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"- via a drop-down menu","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"tucked in the upper right corner of every post -","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"is awkward ,","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"he said ,","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"and does n't allow people to provide links","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"that prove stories are false :","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"`` On a platform","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"where every engagement is very pleasant , almost addictive ,","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"the reporting process feels like something out of Windows 98 . ''","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"Another idea is to make the names of news sources larger and more visible on Facebook posts .","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"At the moment , publication titles are tucked away under posts in a tiny gray font ,","depth":7},{"id":151,"text":"obscuring the fact","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"that false headlines may be coming from familiar-sounding but fringe publications like `` ABCNews.com.co '' and the `` Denver Guardian . ''","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"Fact checkers are also calling on Facebook to share more data","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"on which fake news stories are trafficking especially well on the social network ,","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"so that they can focus their efforts .","depth":6},{"id":156,"text":"Zuckerberg , in his post , suggested","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"that streamlining the feedback loop is a priority .","depth":7},{"id":158,"text":"Among the anti-misinformation projects","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"the company has underway ,","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"wrote the CEO ,","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"is `` easy reporting '' of fake news .","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"He also said","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"the company is exploring labeling false stories ,","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"but provided few details .","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"Facebook hopes to `` learn from '' fact-check organizations .","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"The fact checkers readily admit","depth":7},{"id":168,"text":"they need the power of Facebook","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"to amplify their findings","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"and help stem the tide of fake news .","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"Taken together ,","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"the three organizations have fewer than 20 staffers ,","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"compared with the 1.2 billion people","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"who use Facebook on an average day .","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"`` We 're going to fight it ,","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"but there 's probably thousands of posts every day","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"that are suspicious or fake ,","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"and we 're 10 people , ''","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"says PolitiFact executive director Aaron Sharockman .","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"`` There 's a powerful hose of misinformation","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"and , relatively , we 're an eyedropper . ''","depth":8},{"id":182,"text":"The coming years will be challenging for fact checkers ,","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"given that the incoming president tweets and retweets with abandon ,","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"has a rhetorical style","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"that emphasizes feelings over facts ,","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"and rarely clarifies .","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"Trump 's remarks are often a `` word soup ''","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"and he `` contradicts himself within sentences , ''","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"Sharockman said .","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"Although fact checkers often ask for and get feedback from politicians on what exactly they meant to say ,","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"the Trump campaign `` was incommunicado , ''","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"Kiely said .","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":194,"text":"although many fact checkers believe","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"Facebook is central to solving the problem ,","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"some are wary of making one company the be-all-end-all gatekeeper of what 's true and what 's not .","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"And they concede","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"the task wo n't be easy ,","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"given that questionable stories can be shades of gray","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"- ranging from outright fake to half-true to biased .","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"Any adjustments to News Feed","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"that Facebook does make","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"are likely to trigger a backlash .","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"When a report emerged last spring","depth":12},{"id":205,"text":"suggesting","depth":13},{"id":206,"text":"that the company routinely stripped right-leaning news from its Trending box ,","depth":13},{"id":207,"text":"Republicans and conservative pundits unleashed their ire ,","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"leading to a sit-down in California with Zuckerberg and a pledge by the company","depth":13},{"id":209,"text":"to do better .","depth":13},{"id":210,"text":"`` 'Fake ' has become a catchall for something","depth":13},{"id":211,"text":"you do n't like , ''","depth":13},{"id":212,"text":"Sharockman said .","depth":12},{"id":213,"text":"`` I do n't envy Facebook 's job at all . ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":427,"left":344,"right":426,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":344,"left":324,"right":343,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":324,"left":304,"right":323,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":304,"left":252,"right":303,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":224,"right":251,